main event: One object with a bulky round-cylindrical shape was observed near Farmington, New Mexico on 23 November 1957.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 1.5 minutes., The object was described as bulky and round-cylindrical., The object was positioned near a drilling rig and was seen moving about., The sighting resulted in the object disappearing from view., The report suggests that the sighting was likely an aircraft with contrails.
